law.text:
By resolution, the Board may provide that the State bonds authorized by an enabling act:
be in 1 or more series;
bear a certain date of issue;
be executed in a certain manner;
be sold in a certain manner at public or private, negotiated sale;
be in certain denominations, not necessarily in equal paramounts;
mature in certain amounts at certain times, not necessarily in consecutive annual installments, but not later than 15 years after their respective dates of issue;
bear interest at certain rates or at rates to be determined in the manner stated in the resolution; and
be paid, as to principal and interest, at certain places.
